You first need to determine if you round up or down.  This is by looking at the last number to the left.  If it is larger than 5 you round up, if 5 or smaller you round down.  Now that you know if you are rounding up or down, if the number is in the tens, when you round down, the number in the tens place stays the same, if you round up, you add 1 to the number in the tens place.  And the number in the ones place always goes to zero or 0.  In this case, the number you are rounding is  10.5.  Hence the answer would be 10
